#MongoDB

##Getting Started
*[Google Cloud Shell](https://console.cloud.google.com/home/dashboard?cloudshell=true)
* git clone https://github.com/u1i/mongodb-getting-started
* cd mongodb-getting-started
* ./run-mongo.sh

#Commands

##Databases
* New/switch database: use "Database"
* Check current database: db
* See all databases: show databases
* Deleting database: db.dropDatabase()

##Collections
* New collection: db.createCollection("file", options) 
* See all collections: show collections
* Deleting a collection: db."file".drop()

## CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete)

###Create
* Adding 1 record: db."file".insert({"Key":"Key_value"})
* Adding multiple records: db."file".insertMany({"Key1":"Key_value1","Key2":"Key_value2",...})

###Read
* Reading all records from Collection: db."file".find()
